-- India appoints R Gandhi as deputy governor of central bank for 3 years
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Thu Apr 03, 2014 10:09AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 3 (Reuters) - The Indian government has appointed R Gandhi as deputy governor of the Reserve Bank of India for three years, effective April 3, the central bank said on Thursday.

Gandhi was the executive director at the Reserve Bank of India before being promoted to deputy governor post. Gandhi will look after the department including banking operations and development, non-banking supervision, risk monitoring, urban banks and expenditure and budgetary control.